job_description:
This is Worldline
We are the innovators at the heart of the payments technology industry, shaping how the world pays and gets paid. The solutions our people build today power the growth of millions of businesses tomorrow. From your local coffee shop to unicorns and international banks. From San Francisco to Auckland. We are in every corner of the world, in every part of commerce. And just as we help our customers accelerate their business, we are committed to helping our people accelerate their careers. Together, we shape the evolution.
The Opportunity
At Worldline, our technology addresses persistent challenges of the payment world. We design and operate leading digital payment and transactional solutions that enable sustainable economic growth and reinforce trust and security in our societies. If you are a recent (law) graduate, with 0-3 years of experience, interested in learning the inner workings of a compliance department within a regulated fast-paced multinational as well as gaining exposure to the exciting world of FinTech, then get ready to join our company.
We have many hardworking and dedicated peers that give the best they can every day. We are committed to continuous improvement. We are always looking for new and innovative ways to improve quality, reduce costs, build excellent solutions, and grow customer happiness. We would like to welcome an organized, innovative and process driven colleague to our Financial Security Compliance Team. Eager to learn and the willingness to develop yourself are key. In addition, a critical mindset and pragmatic approach are desired.
You will work for Worldline Digital Commerce (Global Collect Services B.V. and subsidiaries) based in Hoofddorp, close to Amsterdam. Global Collect Services B.V. has a PSD2 license and is supervised by DNB. Worldline Digital Commerce provides one single integration with our global payment platform and connects merchants to markets around the world. Over 150 payment methods and currencies deliver a fully localized payment experience to customers anywhere, on any device. With our Full-Service model merchants are able to collect those payments from around the world without the need for a local bank account or legal entity. The merchants of Worldline Digital Commerce are large global enterprises.
Day-to-Day Responsibilities
The Financial Crime Officer will be working together with the other compliance officers in the following areas:
Develop and execute the Financial Security Annual Plan;
Develop and execute the Financial Security Monitoring Programme;
Conduct Compliance Monitoring on financial crime related topics;
Manage and carry out the Systematic Integrity Risk Analyses;
Provide in-depth training and awareness sessions on financial crime related topics;
Advice other organisational departments on financial crime related topics;
Further professionalize the transaction monitoring framework;
Further professionalize the sanction screening process;
Develop and review policies and procedures on financial crime related topics;
Conduct gap analyses on (new) laws and regulations related to financial crime;
Assist in completing DNB questionnaires and reports;
Develop Compliance Reports for the Financial Security compliance pillar;
Manage compliance oversight by creating dashboards of compliance risks (using e.g. software).
What We Are Looking For
You are following a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree;
You’re interested in compliance and EU Regulations in financial services (e.g., PSD2);
Business oriented, bearing in mind the bigger picture with the compliance risks and independent of mind.
Capacity to search for answers and solve problems, capacity to focus on the final objective.
Interpersonal skills and relationship management.
Capacity to work independently.
Strong team player with high self-motivation and positive attitude.
Eager to learn and the willingness to develop yourself are key.
A critical mindset and pragmatic approach are desired.
Able to read Dutch (Dutch laws).
Perfect fluency (oral and written) in English.
Knowledge in payment industry and payment services is nice to have.
Perks & Benefits
At Worldline you’ll get the chance to be at the heart of the global payments technology industry and shape how the world pays and gets paid. On top of that, you will also:
Use your 29.5 holiday days, based on 40 work hours, to enjoy some time off and recharge!
On target bonus based on your personal performance and the company results.
We pay for your commute when working from the Worldline office.
We offer flexible working hours, so you can adapt to your personal circumstances. Working from home is possible too!
We care for your health. Enjoy the discount on your Health insurance!
You become a member of our pension scheme. Next to the savings we make, you have the option to make savings for when you retire!
Joining the big-league means entering a world of knowledge and wisdom for you to opt-in to. Connect with likeminded colleagues, learn from the best and grow!
Shape the evolution
We are on an exciting journey towards the next frontiers of payments technology, and we look for big thinkers, people with passion, can-do attitude and a hunger to learn and grow. Here you’ll work with ambitious colleagues from around the world, take on unique challenges as a team, and make a real impact on the society. With an empowering culture, strong technology and extensive training opportunities, we help you accelerate your career - wherever you decide to go. Join our global team of 18,000 innovators and shape a tomorrow that is yours to own.

Making a true difference as HEAD OF PORTFOLIO of the Portfolio Investment Team of Aqua-Spark? Are you an inspiring leader and do you want to contribute to creating positive environmental and social impact globally? Aqua-Spark (Forbes, Impact 50) is an investment fund in innovative solutions for food security and ocean conservation through aquaculture. We are currently recruiting for this key role, leading our team of amazingly talented, highly motivated, mission driven portfolio managers. Are you a quick strategic thinker/a doer with an eye for opportunity, solution-oriented, then we welcome your application!

The Job and main responsibilities

As the Head of Portfolio your main responsibility is to lead the growing team of 5- growing into 15 (senior) Portfolio Investment Managers to optimize result for the fund’s investors and portfolio companies within the context of Aqua-Spark’s investment strategy and impact objectives. The position oversees all portfolio management operations and portfolio investment activities. This results in investment recommendations for the Chief Portfolio Officer (CPO) and the Investment Committee. You are responsible for the follow-on investment process of the portfolio companies, which includes a.o. proactive portfolio management and support, in depth due diligence of investee companies, term sheet/deal negotiations. You are strategically involved in Aqua-Spark’s investment strategy, are part of the Management Team, together with the Head of Dealflow, Head of New Deals and Head of Boards. You report directly to the CPO.


Key responsible for …

Making thorough analyses of various investment cases of follow-on investments on portfolio investments, negotiate term sheets, etc.. (coordination of the) the on- and off site in-depth due diligence process on portfolio investments;
Responsible for the investment process regarding follow-on investments, proposals to the investment committee;
Monitor, guide and manage portfolio companies’ performance for both the portfolio company as Aqua-Spark’s investment strategy and objectives; analyzing through KPI’s for the portfolio companies, quarterly reports, support the portfolio to help them strive and thrive, etc.
Lead the department, grow the department and its members. Training the team, team motivation, developing a high performing team;
Cooperation with the Management teams,C-suite and the Portfolio Investment team to set the Key Performance Indicators for the portfolio companies, to monitor both financial and non-financial performance of the existing portfolio investments, and to provide (pro-)active support to portfolio companies to optimize Portfolio results; Closely coordinating with the CIO and CROO on impact and risk;
Making information and learnings available and actionable for the investment team and Aqua-Spark as an organization;
Show leadership and engagement with defining new investment process improvements to promote efficiency and scalability;
Pro-actively build and establish sustainable professional relationships with the worldwide Aqua-Spark network: internal and external stakeholders such as portfolio companies, experts and consultants, investors, etc..


What does it take to be successful working at Aqua-Spark in this position?

Besides a Bachelor’s or Master’s Degree in corporate or commercial law, Business Administration, Economics, or similar discipline, you have 10 or more years of professional working experience in a position with a similar level of responsibility, for example in impact investing, PE/VC, corporate finance or business development.
You have experience with/in …

Closing a variety of investment deals, negotiation, deal structure, due diligence and dealing with an independent investment committee.
You have experience in investing in SME’s/early stage companies as well as later stage. Preferably demonstrable experience with helping to bring early stage SME’s to maturity as an investor. Experience with pre series A, series A, Series B, series C, Series D investment. Making initial investments, but also follow on-Investments;
Successfully leading and supporting and coaching leadership teams;
You have a strong understanding of corporate finance and performance management principles;
Experience working in an International environment, having an international mindset with cultural awareness;
Business planning, negotiating and financial modeling;
Structuring and continuously improving work processes and coordinating external advisors;

Furthermore…

Excellent financial and verbal analytical skills;
Superb written and oral communication skills, with a high degree of professionalism in English, preferably a second language;
Experience working with processing legal documentation/ information is required;
Works independently to successfully contribute to and complete an investment process;
Alignment with Aqua-Spark’s values, preferably understanding of global food production and the agri/aquaculture industry. Eager to learn, knowledge of, experience with and willingness to follow trends and developments in aquaculture. Broad interests with an understanding of the business and financial world and knowledge of trends and current activities in the relevant (financial) markets.
Must be proficient in Microsoft Office; familiarity with databases; excellent IT/computer skills in general;
Board experience, experience with PE and/or IPO is preferred;
Familiarity with diverse business functions such as experience and a good understanding of corporate governance, Investor relations, PR, Finance, etc. is preferred.
Willingness to travel.


Aqua-Spark is a fast growing, global investment fund that makes investments in sustainable aquaculture businesses that generate investment returns while creating positive social and environmental impact. The fund is building an ecosystem of small to medium-sized enterprises across the global aquaculture value chain to make aquaculture more sustainable, healthier and more accessible for all. We work in a great team where communication is key!


What do we offer?
An excellent salary package including participation profit sharing and a truly impactful role within a great entrepreneurial and global organization that is growing fast. Furthermore we offer:

Working in a great Investment team where communication and cooperation is key;
Partly working from home;
Working in an international organization that values inclusivity and diversity;
Traveling;
An excellent introduction, quick integration, and opportunities for professional development;
Working in a challenging international environment collaborating within a great team of professionals, highly motivated, dedicated, mission driven!


Contact information

For more information or if you want to apply directly, contact Marjolein Jetten and/or Sophie van Dongen at marjolein@aqua-spark.nl / sophie@aqua-spark.nl.
